Women lack the noble soul,
the immortal one.

252
00:35:40,817 --> 00:35:46,094
But for a real woman,
even one soul is more than enough,

253
00:35:46,174 --> 00:35:49,573
as long as it blends in with that
of a man, in perfect harmony,

254
00:35:49,652 --> 00:35:52,451
with the fusion of their bodies.

255
00:36:01,606 --> 00:36:06,204
What do you want, Marquese?
Oh, yes. I understand.

256
00:36:10,841 --> 00:36:14,760
She want us to hear the opinion
of her young niece, Edvige,

257
00:36:14,839 --> 00:36:17,118
who is very learned in theology.

258
00:36:18,157 --> 00:36:21,875
What were you studying this morning,
my child?

259
00:36:21,956 --> 00:36:26,313
I was reading Saint Augustine,
which I found absurd.

260
00:36:26,393 --> 00:36:29,752
I think I can disprove
some of his statements.

261
00:36:29,831 --> 00:36:32,510
Which of his statements
did you disprove?

262
00:36:32,590 --> 00:36:35,548
His theory on the mother
of the Savior.

263
00:36:35,629 --> 00:36:40,945
Saint Augustine sustains that Mary
conceived Jesus through her ears.

264
00:36:41,185 --> 00:36:45,903
Do you doubt it?
Yes, for three reasons.

265
00:36:46,222 --> 00:36:49,901
First: because God, since He is not
material substance,

266
00:36:49,981 --> 00:36:55,937
needs no hole through which
to enter or exit.

267
00:36:56,498 --> 00:37:00,775
Second: the hearing tubes do not
communicate with maternal alveolus.

268
00:37:00,855 --> 00:37:04,933
Third: if the Virgin Mary
had conceived through her ears,

269
00:37:05,013 --> 00:37:08,372
she should have given birth
through her ears, right?

270
00:37:08,451 --> 00:37:11,730
But in this case... Excuse me...

271
00:37:11,809 --> 00:37:14,368
In this case,
the Catholics are right

272
00:37:14,448 --> 00:37:20,165
in considering the Virgin,
a virgin before she conceived.

273
00:38:13,018 --> 00:38:18,615
Here is my refuge, my secret church,
my interior dwelling.

274
00:38:19,894 --> 00:38:22,652
My magic laboratory.

275
00:38:22,733 --> 00:38:28,049
Everything you see,
comes from an antique period.

276
00:38:28,250 --> 00:38:32,727
And it arrived here... mysteriously.

277
00:38:33,127 --> 00:38:37,925
Did you recognize it?
It was from the divine Paracelsus.

278
00:38:38,004 --> 00:38:42,482
This liquid has been boiling
for 15 years,

279
00:38:42,562 --> 00:38:46,719
and will have to boil
for another five.

280
00:38:51,478 --> 00:38:53,636
Tell the truth.

281
00:38:53,716 --> 00:38:57,994
You possess the secret
of the philosopher's stone, right?

282
00:38:59,313 --> 00:39:01,192
No. No, madam.

283
00:39:01,272 --> 00:39:03,631
What makes you think that?

284
00:39:05,230 --> 00:39:07,869
My dear friend

285
00:39:08,908 --> 00:39:11,147
you can trust me.

286
00:39:11,227 --> 00:39:14,665
I know you have the famous stone

287
00:39:14,745 --> 00:39:19,702
and also the capacity to communicate
with the spirits of the 4 elements.

288
00:39:19,783 --> 00:39:24,940
You could overthrow
the King of France at any time.

289
00:39:25,020 --> 00:39:27,978
I would never dare.
I love France.

290
00:39:28,338 --> 00:39:30,457
You over-estimate me, my friend.

291
00:39:33,135 --> 00:39:36,254
Giacomo, I beg you,

292
00:39:36,334 --> 00:39:38,772
help me in the great work.

293
00:39:40,212 --> 00:39:43,490
The great work?
What do you mean?

294
00:39:44,610 --> 00:39:47,608
Please, you know what it is about.

295
00:39:47,808 --> 00:39:49,367
Speak.

296
00:39:53,405 --> 00:39:55,764
I have to die,

297
00:39:56,523 --> 00:39:59,521
and at the moment of my death

298
00:39:59,641 --> 00:40:02,600
I will be transformed into a man...

299
00:40:02,960 --> 00:40:06,958
A man who will live in eternity!

300
00:40:07,038 --> 00:40:11,035
But this is possible
only if I am fecundated

301
00:40:11,116 --> 00:40:14,314
by an initiate
of my same pyramidal sign.

302
00:40:16,473 --> 00:40:21,790
At the moment of birth, my soul
will enter in the newborn's body

303
00:40:22,470 --> 00:40:26,268
and I will no longer exist
as a woman,

304
00:40:26,348 --> 00:40:29,386
but will go back to living
as a man.

305
00:40:29,466 --> 00:40:33,464
A man who will live forever!

306
00:40:35,263 --> 00:40:38,661
You, without a doubt,

307
00:40:38,741 --> 00:40:43,619
are the man who was sent to me
to help me carry out

308
00:40:45,298 --> 00:40:48,776
this great work.

309
00:40:51,735 --> 00:40:55,772
My dear friend, why are you crying?

310
00:40:56,012 --> 00:40:58,051
It is nothing.

311
00:41:00,450 --> 00:41:04,968
Nothing, really.
Show me your other treasures.

312
00:41:07,286 --> 00:41:09,166
Please, Madam.

313
00:41:26,516 --> 00:41:28,476
All this will be yours

314
00:41:28,555 --> 00:41:32,233
when together we will have created
the great work.

315
00:41:32,793 --> 00:41:34,752
Oh, no!

316
00:41:35,312 --> 00:41:41,389
I did not mean material treasures,
but spiritual ones.

317
00:41:42,628 --> 00:41:46,346
The treasures of your
ultra-terrestrial knowledge.

318
00:41:56,540 --> 00:41:58,900
My dear Giacomo,

319
00:41:59,179 --> 00:42:04,137
the divine Anael has already painted
your portrait in a dream for me.

320
00:42:04,216 --> 00:42:06,175
And I knew...

321
00:42:07,135 --> 00:42:08,495
Be silent.

322
00:42:18,449 --> 00:42:20,248
I am in Paris!

323
00:42:21,847 --> 00:42:24,366
You are in Paris!

324
00:42:25,766 --> 00:42:29,883
Beautiful Paris,
the city of the Mazzarinos,

325
00:42:29,963 --> 00:42:34,201
the Racines, the Voltaires!
Paris!

326
00:42:35,600 --> 00:42:41,477
My young and greedy heart
sings a voluptuous hymn of glory!

327
00:42:52,512 --> 00:42:56,069
The sudden overturning of
the carriage which frightened me,

328
00:42:56,149 --> 00:42:58,428
was maybe a help from destiny.

329
00:42:58,548 --> 00:43:01,426
In fact, he who had almost ended up
under the wheels,

330
00:43:01,507 --> 00:43:04,505
was non-the-less
than my abbey brother,

331
00:43:04,585 --> 00:43:07,583
who some time ago
left Venice and his priest's cassock

332
00:43:07,663 --> 00:43:09,702
to lead a decadent life in Paris,

333
00:43:09,783 --> 00:43:12,101
together with a young red haired
woman from Treviso,

334
00:43:12,181 --> 00:43:14,859
who had incautiously given in
to his flattery.

335
00:43:24,895 --> 00:43:27,613
I eliminated that dirty liar
with a few coins

336
00:43:27,693 --> 00:43:31,211
and brought with me the girl, who,
besides being attractive and witty,

337
00:43:31,291 --> 00:43:35,369
would have been the ideal person
in my plan for the Marquise.

338
00:43:35,569 --> 00:43:38,007
I planned on talking to her
about it.

339
00:44:10,791 --> 00:44:12,110
Selene.

340
00:44:12,189 --> 00:44:13,909
Anubis.

341
00:44:13,989 --> 00:44:15,948
Osiris.

342
00:44:23,544 --> 00:44:26,502
Let us go beyond
the pleasures of the flesh.

343
00:44:26,582 --> 00:44:30,780
Let us concentrate on melting
our souls together in perfect unison.

344
00:44:30,860 --> 00:44:32,979
Scent of Venus!

345
00:44:33,059 --> 00:44:35,058
Love is the source
and root of life.

346
00:44:35,138 --> 00:44:38,536
Love generates both good and bad
impulses and passions.

347
00:44:38,616 --> 00:44:42,334
Love generates the eternal flame,
both divine as well as human.

348
00:44:42,414 --> 00:44:45,772
Love generates gods and demons.

349
00:44:48,650 --> 00:44:50,569
Take her in your arms.

350
00:44:50,689 --> 00:44:52,649
Come, madam.

351
00:44:57,367 --> 00:44:59,205
Come closer.

352
00:44:59,725 --> 00:45:01,804
Scent of Venus.

353
00:45:36,546 --> 00:45:39,943
Giacomo, the hour of Venus has come.

354
00:45:40,024 --> 00:45:43,982
I am yours.
May the great work be accomplished.

355
00:45:44,062 --> 00:45:45,621
Wait.

356
00:45:45,820 --> 00:45:48,499
I must first complete
my calculations.

357
00:45:52,977 --> 00:45:55,775
I think we are still
in the hour of Mars.

358
00:45:59,013 --> 00:46:00,973
Marcolina.

359
00:46:04,571 --> 00:46:06,130
Come here.

360
00:46:07,850 --> 00:46:10,808
Turn around. I cannot do it.
Bend over.

361
00:46:11,647 --> 00:46:14,446
Never does a man fall
into the deep abyss

362
00:46:14,526 --> 00:46:16,805
and then with equal violence
is thrown up

363
00:46:18,124 --> 00:46:21,043
towards he who is perfection,

364
00:46:21,122 --> 00:46:24,080
like that diaphanous instant

365
00:46:24,161 --> 00:46:26,800
in which the essence of his virility
reaches and touches

366
00:46:26,879 --> 00:46:28,719
the root of the opposite sex.

367
00:46:28,798 --> 00:46:30,518
There, there!

368
00:46:41,752 --> 00:46:43,591
Now silence.

369
00:46:44,030 --> 00:46:45,909
Silence.

370
00:46:57,624 --> 00:47:00,022
Love.
Yes.

371
00:47:26,248 --> 00:47:27,808
Marcolina.

372
00:47:29,326 --> 00:47:30,486
Move.

373
00:47:34,604 --> 00:47:36,163
Closer. Come!

374
00:47:37,283 --> 00:47:38,762
Uncover it.

375
00:48:09,386 --> 00:48:12,225
I can do it. I can do it!

376
00:48:15,463 --> 00:48:17,982
I will pierce you!
I will open you up!

377
00:48:18,981 --> 00:48:21,340
I can do it!
Good boy!

378
00:48:37,611 --> 00:48:40,769
Sirs! Sirs!

379
00:48:40,969 --> 00:48:42,368
Two years later, in Forli',

380
00:48:42,448 --> 00:48:46,446
I was to meet the greatest
love of my life.

381
00:48:46,846 --> 00:48:49,164
Requested by some policemen,
I had gotten myself

382
00:48:49,245 --> 00:48:52,244
into a furious brawl
which started in an inn.

383
00:48:52,803 --> 00:48:56,041
The man in the adjacent room
had been accused by the Pope's guards

384
00:48:56,121 --> 00:48:59,200
of having let a woman in,
dressed as a man.

385
00:49:01,638 --> 00:49:05,116
Put down that sword
or I will be forced to fire!

386
00:49:05,197 --> 00:49:08,795
The host declares that last night
he asked for a lodging

387
00:49:08,875 --> 00:49:13,512
with a young officer who this
morning he discovered was a woman.

388
00:49:13,592 --> 00:49:16,951
He has been screaming like a madman
and slaps that document in our face.

389
00:49:17,030 --> 00:49:18,230
Do you understand
what is written in it?

390
00:49:18,309 --> 00:49:20,549
This gentleman is Hungarian.

391
00:49:20,628 --> 00:49:24,027
He is a Hungarian officer,
so you are committing a violation.

392
00:49:24,107 --> 00:49:26,465
We were called by the host!

393
00:49:26,546 --> 00:49:30,343
Yes. I don't want to go to jail. You
cannot joke with the Holy Father!

394
00:49:30,423 --> 00:49:32,382
Enough!

395
00:49:33,462 --> 00:49:35,101
Bring the coffee!
It is a scandal!

396
00:50:00,287 --> 00:50:02,367
I am French.

397
00:50:03,566 --> 00:50:04,965
My name is Henriette.

398
00:50:06,205 --> 00:50:08,323
What language do you speak
with your lover?

399
00:50:08,404 --> 00:50:11,482
We do not speak.
It has no use in what we do.

400
00:50:17,999 --> 00:50:20,477
Whoever takes a journey to Parma

401
00:50:20,557 --> 00:50:23,675
must be prepared to know at least
three divinities:

402
00:50:23,756 --> 00:50:25,635
salami, ham

403
00:50:25,714 --> 00:50:29,233
and the famous third one...
Parmesan cheese.

404
00:50:32,071 --> 00:50:34,670
I asked myself who
this young lady was.

405
00:50:35,150 --> 00:50:37,108
What is her relationship
with this Hungarian

406
00:50:37,189 --> 00:50:39,307
who could be her father?

407
00:50:39,947 --> 00:50:41,946
Does she have a husband in Parma?

408
00:50:42,266 --> 00:50:47,623
Or in her libertine frenzy, does she
look for other lovers and pleasures?

409
00:51:02,136 --> 00:51:05,174
The captain seemed to have read
my thoughts.

410
00:51:05,254 --> 00:51:06,973
In his bad grammar Latin,
he told me

411
00:51:07,053 --> 00:51:10,931
that even he knew nothing about
this lovely and mysterious lady.

412
00:51:11,011 --> 00:51:13,449
She had turned to him,
asking for protection

413
00:51:13,530 --> 00:51:16,488
as if she feared something
or someone.

414
00:51:16,927 --> 00:51:20,885
But now he had to leave her,
having to go up north.

415
00:51:21,166 --> 00:51:23,284
I could have taken care of her.

416
00:51:41,275 --> 00:51:42,834
Why do you look at me like that?

417
00:51:45,033 --> 00:51:47,072
You do not recognize me anymore?

418
00:51:47,592 --> 00:51:51,390
I feel unimportant next to you.
I cannot call you by your first name.

419
00:51:51,589 --> 00:51:55,748
You are no longer the brave
and bizarre officer I knew.

420
00:52:05,262 --> 00:52:08,820
I will always remain the same girl.

421
00:52:09,460 --> 00:52:12,818
She who had three moments of madness
in her life.

422
00:52:12,898 --> 00:52:18,736
And the last, wonderful madness
was knowing you.

423
00:52:28,211 --> 00:52:31,529
We were invited to a concert
at the hunchback Du Bois' home.

424
00:52:31,608 --> 00:52:35,407
He was an eccentric gentleman
with uncertain amorous boundaries,

425
00:52:35,487 --> 00:52:37,326
just as uncertain were
the boundaries of the Parma dukedom,

426
00:52:37,406 --> 00:52:39,764
divided between the Spanish
and the French.

427
00:52:40,444 --> 00:52:43,402
That evening, two civilizations,
two opposite conceptions of life,

428
00:52:43,482 --> 00:52:45,641
faced each other.

429
00:52:45,722 --> 00:52:49,200
An antique proverb says,

430
00:52:49,279 --> 00:52:51,838
"What is lighter than a feather?

431
00:52:53,637 --> 00:52:54,796
Ashes.

432
00:52:54,876 --> 00:52:57,236
And what is lighter than ashes?

433
00:52:58,395 --> 00:52:59,913
The wind.

434
00:52:59,994 --> 00:53:01,513
And lighter than the wind?

435
00:53:01,593 --> 00:53:03,152
Woman.

436
00:53:03,232 --> 00:53:05,111
And lighter than woman?

437
00:53:05,191 --> 00:53:06,790
Nothing."

438
00:53:06,870 --> 00:53:10,189
We exercise much power over women,
much tyranny,

439
00:53:10,268 --> 00:53:13,586
and we made them accept it
only because

440
00:53:13,667 --> 00:53:16,105
they are kinder,

441
00:53:16,186 --> 00:53:18,424
more reasonable,

442
00:53:18,504 --> 00:53:20,383
more generous than man.

443
00:53:20,463 --> 00:53:24,221
Such qualities which should have made
them superior to us,

444
00:53:24,301 --> 00:53:26,860
instead, put them at our mercy,

445
00:53:26,940 --> 00:53:31,058
because men, in fact, are a hundred
times more unreasonable,

446
00:53:31,138 --> 00:53:32,937
more cruel, violent.

447
00:53:33,016 --> 00:53:35,855
They are more inclined
by nature, to oppress.

448
00:53:35,975 --> 00:53:40,253
Women's kisses are like a glass
of wine.

449
00:53:40,332 --> 00:53:43,691
You drink and drink,
and drink... and then succumb.

450
00:53:43,771 --> 00:53:48,289
He who never speaks badly of women,
does not love them.

451
00:53:49,088 --> 00:53:54,885
Because to understand them and love
them, you must suffer for them.

452
00:53:54,965 --> 00:53:57,723
So then, and only then,

453
00:53:58,644 --> 00:54:01,321
can you find happiness
on the lips of your beloved.

454
00:54:01,402 --> 00:54:06,200
A kiss is just the desire
of devouring what you kiss.

455
00:54:07,279 --> 00:54:11,437
I really think that Du Bois
has that sort of appetite!

456
00:54:12,876 --> 00:54:14,635
What is a kiss?

457
00:54:15,234 --> 00:54:18,712
Simply the desire to get lost

458
00:54:18,793 --> 00:54:20,712
in the soul of the woman you love.

459
00:54:44,580 --> 00:54:46,978
We are beginning!

460
00:54:47,058 --> 00:54:50,816
Silence. You will see
a lovely performance.

461
00:56:02,259 --> 00:56:05,257
He himself embroidered
his costume.

462
00:57:53,041 --> 00:57:55,360
It is all metaphoric.

463
00:59:37,346 --> 00:59:39,265
The boy is good too!

464
00:59:39,345 --> 00:59:42,064
He is very handsome!
Bravo!

465
00:59:48,580 --> 00:59:52,058
He was extraordinary. Do you not
agree? You loved him, right?

466
00:59:52,139 --> 00:59:57,975
The music made me cry,
but I did not understand the story.

467
00:59:59,935 --> 01:00:02,773
I do not deserve so much applause.

468
01:00:02,852 --> 01:00:06,451
I wrote this work
for Giambruno.

469
01:00:06,531 --> 01:00:09,689
Thank you, Giambruno.

470
01:00:10,329 --> 01:00:11,528
Bravo.
Thank you.

471
01:00:11,608 --> 01:00:14,687
My sincere compliments
for the virtuoso singer

472
01:00:14,767 --> 01:00:17,525
and the mime instructor.
Amazing.

473
01:00:17,725 --> 01:00:20,804
But after the topics discussed
at the table,

474
01:00:20,883 --> 01:00:24,282
you will not be surprised
of my absolute disapproval

475
01:00:24,362 --> 01:00:28,080
of the idea behind
your captivating ballet.

476
01:01:24,170 --> 01:01:27,129
Who is this Enrichetta?

477
01:01:27,729 --> 01:01:32,167
Who is this priceless treasure
of which I have become owner?

478
01:01:32,246 --> 01:01:34,645
Is it really possible?

479
01:01:34,964 --> 01:01:37,843
Oh, stars! You tell me!

480
01:01:38,403 --> 01:01:40,802
Cry it out from the depth
of your sky,

481
01:01:40,882 --> 01:01:44,160
that the happy mortal
to which this creature belongs to,

482
01:01:44,240 --> 01:01:46,039
is Giacomo Casanova. Only him!

483
01:01:47,078 --> 01:01:49,917
Mister Casanova,
what is the matter?

484
01:01:50,676 --> 01:01:54,955
My friend, I am afraid.
I am afraid of my happiness.

485
01:01:55,034 --> 01:01:56,673
Yes?
Enrichetta...

486
01:01:56,754 --> 01:02:01,190
She is an extraordinary woman,
with an extraordinary destiny.

487
01:02:01,271 --> 01:02:04,829
However, I am tempted...
Forgive me, gentlemen.

488
01:02:06,628 --> 01:02:08,627
Mister D'Antoine.

489
01:02:08,747 --> 01:02:13,984
Wonderful!
A real concert player!

490
01:02:14,064 --> 01:02:17,742
Where did you learn so well?
In the convent.

491
01:02:18,182 --> 01:02:20,461
But if it was not for a precise
order from the bishop,

492
01:02:20,541 --> 01:02:23,819
the abbess would never have given
me permission to play.

493
01:02:23,899 --> 01:02:27,137
That pious wife of Christ, said that
when I played the violoncello

494
01:02:27,217 --> 01:02:29,816
I always had an indecent pose.

495
01:02:30,575 --> 01:02:34,653
Mademoiselle, I apologize
for being so late.

496
01:02:35,293 --> 01:02:37,252
The trip is long.

497
01:02:54,922 --> 01:02:59,281
Always, always with you,
my sweet Enrichetta.

498
01:02:59,880 --> 01:03:04,318
Cruel Enrichetta,
how many things you hide from me.

499
01:03:04,398 --> 01:03:08,276
Your past, your virtues,
your talents.

500
01:03:08,355 --> 01:03:10,595
When I heard you play
the violoncello,

501
01:03:10,675 --> 01:03:13,633
you almost made me die.

