in saying I am just a"cabalon".

993
01:58:13,900 --> 01:58:17,858
My name is known in all of Europe.

994
01:58:17,939 --> 01:58:19,978
I am considered a literary person.

995
01:58:20,137 --> 01:58:22,017
A brilliant business man.

996
01:58:23,735 --> 01:58:26,294
I do not understand German well,
Mother. What are you saying?

997
01:58:26,374 --> 01:58:29,732
You do not understand
or do not want to?

998
01:58:32,651 --> 01:58:36,889
I could find a house in the country,
maybe next to yours.

999
01:58:36,968 --> 01:58:40,727
I have 400 sequins.
I can give you half if you want.

1000
01:58:41,286 --> 01:58:45,204
I intend to stop running around
the world. I am no longer young.

1001
01:58:45,804 --> 01:58:48,283
Do you have news of our relatives?

1002
01:58:48,362 --> 01:58:51,321
I also hope to return to Venice,
as soon as...

1003
01:59:47,292 --> 01:59:50,130
I did not even ask for her address!

1004
01:59:59,205 --> 02:00:02,484
I went to Holland, to Belgium,
to Spain.

1005
02:00:02,923 --> 02:00:05,402
In Oslo, I became seriously ill.

1006
02:00:05,482 --> 02:00:07,361
Finally I reached Wurtemberg,

1007
02:00:07,441 --> 02:00:10,719
which, at the time, was the most
brilliant court of Europe.

1008
02:00:49,459 --> 02:00:53,777
I would like to ask you, madam,
since you wisely influence the duke,

1009
02:00:53,856 --> 02:00:57,694
could you not suggest to him to
offer me the position of ambassador

1010
02:00:57,775 --> 02:01:02,692
to the court of Saxony?
The prince highly respects me.

1011
02:01:37,074 --> 02:01:40,992
I have a letter from his excellency
Cardinal Lowrier.

1012
02:01:41,072 --> 02:01:44,830
He kindly accepted
to recommend me to you.

1013
02:01:44,910 --> 02:01:47,789
I would like to submit
to the attention of your...

1014
02:02:15,574 --> 02:02:18,973
In my country, turtles are a sign
of good luck, Highness.

1015
02:03:12,705 --> 02:03:15,703
Here are the designs
for a new type of fortress

1016
02:03:15,783 --> 02:03:18,141
based on three principles
of Democritus and Leucippus.

1017
02:03:18,222 --> 02:03:20,580
I know that your war
at the borders...

1018
02:04:01,839 --> 02:04:03,478
Observe these seeds, Highness.

1019
02:04:03,557 --> 02:04:07,275
They produce a repulsive
red efflurescence,

1020
02:04:07,356 --> 02:04:10,634
but it has miraculous virtues.
It was discovered by a Spanish monk

1021
02:04:10,714 --> 02:04:14,312
who experimented it many times
on himself.

1022
02:04:14,432 --> 02:04:18,590
Nobody in the world could say
that man is over 40,

1023
02:04:18,669 --> 02:04:22,348
but he actually is over one hundred.

1024
02:04:24,867 --> 02:04:27,505
Princess,
I am desperate in my love for you

1025
02:04:27,585 --> 02:04:29,464
but your heart is of iron!

1026
02:04:29,544 --> 02:04:32,263
And your buttocks is of wood!

1027
02:04:34,942 --> 02:04:37,060
Never in my life

1028
02:04:37,140 --> 02:04:40,258
have I been so insulted!

1029
02:04:40,858 --> 02:04:43,537
I will no longer permit
that he come before my eyes,

1030
02:04:43,616 --> 02:04:47,175
even if I am in this palace,
and my duty as a guest

1031
02:04:47,255 --> 02:04:50,253
does not allow me to take up
my sword!

1032
02:04:50,333 --> 02:04:53,691
Go away, scoundrels,
back to your sewers!

1033
02:05:05,325 --> 02:05:10,123
My brother, the Duke, says you
frightened Rosalba with your sword.

1034
02:05:10,203 --> 02:05:15,200
That is not good for a Latin
lover of beautiful women as you are.

1035
02:05:15,280 --> 02:05:16,599
Enchanting!

1036
02:05:16,680 --> 02:05:20,518
I heard that in Nuremberg
a general had built

1037
02:05:20,597 --> 02:05:26,035
a mechanical chess player,
but this goes beyond any imagination.

1038
02:05:26,875 --> 02:05:30,152
Look! It is perfect!

1039
02:05:30,233 --> 02:05:33,231
One could swear it is real flesh.

1040
02:05:34,150 --> 02:05:35,750
The right color.

1041
02:05:36,669 --> 02:05:38,668
It would fool anyone.

1042
02:06:48,071 --> 02:06:51,350
It is very late.
Are you still up?

1043
02:10:20,121 --> 02:10:25,678
I hope you will excuse me,
Madam, for the liberty I took.

1044
02:10:25,758 --> 02:10:29,316
But I so much wish
to see what you are, naturally.

1045
02:10:29,596 --> 02:10:31,555
You do not protest?

1046
02:10:35,792 --> 02:10:38,511
What sort of mad inventor
was your father?

1047
02:10:38,831 --> 02:10:44,108
Certainly mad, but a poet,
if he made you so beautiful.

1048
02:10:45,867 --> 02:10:49,465
Did he incestuously possess you?

1049
02:10:51,065 --> 02:10:54,343
You excite me
with your secret silence.

1050
02:10:54,423 --> 02:10:56,942
Will you lie down with me?

1051
02:10:57,021 --> 02:11:01,539
Will you give your delicate
mechanism to my eagerness?

1052
02:11:02,778 --> 02:11:05,097
Yes? Oh, yes!

1053
02:11:11,893 --> 02:11:13,373
You are beautiful, you know?

1054
02:11:14,253 --> 02:11:17,411
Do not refuse.
What is your name?

1055
02:11:17,890 --> 02:11:19,569
Oh, Rosalba!

1056
02:11:20,449 --> 02:11:24,167
No, Rosalba. You are called love!
Love!

1057
02:11:26,086 --> 02:11:29,085
That is your name!
Do you know that?

1058
02:11:29,485 --> 02:11:32,523
I have been looking for you forever.

1059
02:11:34,002 --> 02:11:36,601
Beautiful! Child!

1060
02:11:54,792 --> 02:11:57,670
My beautiful devil!

1061
02:12:04,346 --> 02:12:07,305
Love. Give it to me!

1062
02:14:40,465 --> 02:14:43,543
The winter is very long in Bohemia.

1063
02:14:43,623 --> 02:14:48,460
For many years I have been living
in Dux, in the Waldenstein castle.

1064
02:14:48,541 --> 02:14:51,459
I am a librarian for the count.

1065
02:14:51,539 --> 02:14:57,176
An important assignment that
is fit for my studious character,

1066
02:14:57,256 --> 02:14:59,895
for a man of literature.

1067
02:15:25,561 --> 02:15:27,960
Do you feel better this evening?
It is very warm.

1068
02:15:41,713 --> 02:15:45,631
My macaroni!
I want my macaroni!

1069
02:15:45,711 --> 02:15:49,069
I did not prepare macaroni
this evening. No macaroni!

1070
02:15:49,149 --> 02:15:51,868
If you want,
there is goat fried brain.

1071
02:15:51,948 --> 02:15:57,225
I clearly said I want macaroni
on my plate every evening!

1072
02:15:57,304 --> 02:16:00,503
If that is not possible,
the count will be informed.

1073
02:16:00,583 --> 02:16:03,661
There is polenta,
which is almost ready.

1074
02:16:04,701 --> 02:16:06,820
I do not want polenta!

1075
02:16:06,899 --> 02:16:12,377
I cannot stand that my dinner
be disturbed by such people!

1076
02:16:12,457 --> 02:16:16,095
Mister Casanova,
your agreement with the count

1077
02:16:16,175 --> 02:16:19,293
dispenses you from eating
with the servants and the troops.

1078
02:16:20,493 --> 02:16:22,731
Then why do you give us
this honor?

1079
02:16:22,812 --> 02:16:25,890
Listen, Faulkircher.

1080
02:16:25,969 --> 02:16:30,208
Only because of one
of life's cruel turn of events,

1081
02:16:30,287 --> 02:16:33,206
that the two of us met.

1082
02:16:33,326 --> 02:16:37,004
You, a butler,
and I a librarian.

1083
02:16:37,084 --> 02:16:42,441
Respect my solitude and keep away
from me!

1084
02:16:42,521 --> 02:16:44,840
You are a cheating scoundrel!

1085
02:16:44,920 --> 02:16:50,317
You take advantage of the count's
absence, but he will find out!

1086
02:16:50,396 --> 02:16:53,116
Also that you practice

1087
02:16:53,195 --> 02:17:00,552
anti-physical attractions
with your Viderol. You disgust me!

1088
02:17:00,631 --> 02:17:04,189
Go ahead and speak
in your vulgar German!

1089
02:17:04,270 --> 02:17:06,069
Who understands you?

1090
02:17:06,149 --> 02:17:11,666
I am an artist, a writer.
I do not mingle with certain people.

1091
02:17:11,745 --> 02:17:14,944
He is an artist too,
a very talented actor.

1092
02:17:15,024 --> 02:17:17,423
It disgusts me to talk to you.

1093
02:17:17,502 --> 02:17:20,461
Do not be so arrogant, Casanova.

1094
02:17:20,541 --> 02:17:24,379
You are a servant of the count
of Waldenstein, like us. A servant!

1095
02:17:24,459 --> 02:17:26,737
Disgusting! You are disgusting!

1096
02:17:32,655 --> 02:17:38,092
I received the greatest insult ever,
in this place.

1097
02:17:38,172 --> 02:17:41,970
That portrait has been hung up
with a disgusting substance.

1098
02:17:42,050 --> 02:17:45,808
The person responsible is Faulkircher
or his deprived lover Viderol.

1099
02:17:46,167 --> 02:17:50,086
Which of the two furnished
the fecal material, I do not know,

1100
02:17:50,166 --> 02:17:53,244
considering their terrible
relationship

1101
02:17:53,324 --> 02:17:57,162
which easily enables
mixture of that substance.

1102
02:17:57,762 --> 02:18:01,960
Observe.
It is a very similar portrait.

1103
02:18:08,236 --> 02:18:13,873
It was printed as an illustration
in my famous novel"Icosameron".

1104
02:18:14,593 --> 02:18:16,952
Did you read it by chance?

1105
02:18:17,391 --> 02:18:19,510
I will offer you a copy, if I may.

1106
02:18:19,591 --> 02:18:25,787
I think that after my death there
will be talk of me for some time,

1107
02:18:25,867 --> 02:18:31,184
as author of that work.
I am a famous Italian writer.

1108
02:18:37,141 --> 02:18:40,180
You surely know my name.

1109
02:18:42,858 --> 02:18:46,457
Giacomo Casanova from Venice.

1110
02:18:47,736 --> 02:18:49,175
A literary man,

1111
02:18:49,815 --> 02:18:51,374
a philosopher...

1112
02:18:56,172 --> 02:18:59,849
It is not for a whim
that I come to you, Countess,

1113
02:18:59,929 --> 02:19:04,407
but to implore justice
for a poor old man.

1114
02:19:04,807 --> 02:19:11,323
That shady individual, Faulkircher,
and that Viderol

1115
02:19:11,483 --> 02:19:14,681
find many pretexts to torment me.

1116
02:19:14,762 --> 02:19:18,679
They broke the door of the library,
and took away books.

1117
02:19:18,759 --> 02:19:22,918
And they blame me
for their disappearance!

1118
02:19:22,997 --> 02:19:25,556
And I have not eaten macaroni
since Wednesday!

1119
02:19:26,475 --> 02:19:30,594
These unpleasant happenings
disturb my activity as writer.

1120
02:19:30,873 --> 02:19:33,312
What should I do, Countess?

1121
02:19:34,871 --> 02:19:39,429
When my son returns,
he will take care of everything.

1122
02:19:43,746 --> 02:19:49,064
There is a crane
above the wood-shack roof.

1123
02:20:08,134 --> 02:20:10,772
I want you to meet Giacomo Casanova,

1124
02:20:11,572 --> 02:20:15,449
an Italian adventurer
who there has been much talk about.

1125
02:20:22,446 --> 02:20:24,005
Giacomo!

1126
02:20:24,804 --> 02:20:29,443
Come. We are waiting for you.
My friends want to hear you.

1127
02:20:29,522 --> 02:20:31,761
Recite something.

1128
02:24:14,324 --> 02:24:15,684
Venice!

1129
02:24:20,201 --> 02:24:23,080
Will I ever return to Venice?

1130
02:24:26,838 --> 02:24:28,397
The other night...

1131
02:24:31,116 --> 02:24:32,555
I had a dream...

1132
02:25:00,380 --> 02:25:01,460
Isabella.

